[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: Emese Szasz wins epee gold for Hungary

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Emese Szasz delivered Hungary's first gold medal at Rio 2016 with victory over Italy's Rossella Fiamingo in the final of the women's individual epee.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Szasz had trailed two-time world champion Fiamingo 11-7 during the second period.
But she fought back to win 15-13 and earn Hungary a third gold medal in the women's epee in the last five Olympics.
Earlier, China's Yiwen Sun took bronze, beating Lauren Rembi of France, also by a score of 15-13, at Carioca Arena 3.
